{"title_page": "Latrice Royale", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Latrice Royale\n| alt                = \n| image              = Latrice Royale singing.jpg\n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = Timothy Wilcots\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1972|02|12}}\n| birth_place        = [[Torrance, California]], U.S.\n| death_date         = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} or {{Death-date and age|death date\u2020|birth date\u2020}} -->\n| death_place        = \n| nationality        = American\n| spouse             = {{Marriage|Christopher Hamblin|2018}}\n| residence          = [[Hollywood, Florida]], U.S.\n| other_names        = \n| occupation         = [[Drag performer]]\n| known_for          = {{unbulleted list|[[RuPaul's Drag Race (season 4)|''RuPaul's Drag Race'' (season 4)]]|[[RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars (season 1)|''RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars'' (season 1)]]|[[RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars (season 4)|''RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars'' (season 4)]]}}\n| awards             = ''RuPaul's Drag Race'': Miss Congeniality 2012\n| website            = {{URL|http://latriceroyale.com/}}\n}}\n\n'''Timothy Wilcots'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newnownext.com/latrice-royale-reflects-on-restoration-of-voting-rights/11/2018/| title=Latrice Royale Reflects On Restoration of Voting Rights|publisher=[[Logo (TV network)|Logo]]| first= Lamar |last=Dawson |date= November 9, 2018|accessdate=January 6, 2019}}</ref> (born February 12, 1972),<ref name=\"birthday\">{{cite news|last1=Hagwood|first1=Rod Stafford|title=Two local female impersonators compete on 'RuPaul's Drag Race'|url=http://articles.sun-sentinel.com/2012-01-28/entertainment/fl-features-rupaul-drag-race-locals-012912-20120128_1_rupaul-prize-money-gay-audience|accessdate=23 March 2017|publisher=Sun Sentinel|date=28 Jan 2012}}</ref><ref name=Quorum1 /> better known by the stage name '''Latrice Royale''', is an American [[drag performer]], recording artist, and reality television personality. He is best known for his appearances in [[RuPaul's Drag Race (season 4)|season 4 of ''RuPaul's Drag Race'']] in 2012, and [[RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars (season 1)|season 1]] and [[RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars (season 4)|season 4]] of ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars]]''.  He finished fourth place in the fourth season of ''RuPaul's Drag Race''; in the final episode of the season, he was crowned Miss Congeniality. He placed fifth in the fourth season of ''RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars''. ''[[New York (magazine)|New York]]'' magazine named Royale one of the top 100 Most Powerful Drag Queens in America in June 2019.<ref name=\"nymag\">{{cite news |url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/06/most-powerful-drag-queens-in-america-ranked.html# |title=The Most Powerful Drag Queens in America: Ranking the new establishment. |author=The Editors |date=June 10, 2019 |access-date=June 10, 2019 |magazine=[[New York (magazine)|New York]] |publisher=New York Media, LLC |archive-date=June 10, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190610184458/https://www.vulture.com/2019/06/most-powerful-drag-queens-in-america-ranked.html |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Life and career==\nWilcots was born in [[California]] and raised in [[Compton, California|Compton]], a city in [[Greater Los Angeles]].<ref>[http://latriceroyale.com/about/ Latrice Royale Official Website: About]</ref> While growing up, he did not have a relationship with his father.<ref name=Quorum1>{{cite news|last1=Moffo|first1=Michael|title=Latrice Royale & her Columbus Court|url=http://quorumcolumbus.com/36/post/2013/08/latrice-royale-her-columbus-court.html#.VIvTmzHF98E|accessdate=December 13, 2014|publisher=Quorum Columbus|date=August 20, 2013}}</ref>\n\nRoyale's first foray into drag was dressing up as [[List of In Living Color sketches#W|Wanda]], a character from American [[sketch comedy]] show ''[[In Living Color]]'', to amuse his friends. While in his twenties, in the mid-1990s, he performed in his first [[drag show]]: it was at the Copa Night Club in [[Fort Lauderdale, Florida]].<ref name=Givens1>{{cite news|last1=Givens|first1=Orie|title=RPDR Season 4\u2019s Latrice Royale Whirls and Twirls On CBUS Stages|url=http://outlookcolumbus.com/2012/04/rpdr-season-4s-latrice-royale-whirls-and-twirls-on-cbus-stages/|accessdate=December 13, 2014|publisher=Outlook Columbus|date= April 25, 2012}}</ref> Her drag mother is Tiffany Arieagus.<ref>https://theabbynormal.wordpress.com/2014/08/06/latrice-royale-is-a-queen-of-grace/ added 2/23/2019</ref>\n\nIn May 2011, ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race]]'', a drag competition produced as [[reality television]], opened auditions for the show's fourth season;<ref>{{cite web |url=https://thegavoice.com/culture/rupauls-drag-race-now-casting-for-season-4/ |title=''RuPaul\u2019s Drag Race'' now casting for season 4 |author=<!-- staff --> |date=May 11, 2011 |website=TheGAVoice.com |publisher=[[Georgia Voice]] |access-date=2018-06-30}}</ref> acting on a dare, Wilcots submitted an audition video. His audition was accepted, and he was cast for the show; production began later that year. The fourth season premiered on January 30, 2012. Wilcots was eliminated from the competition in the 11th episode, which aired on April 9, 2012. Viewers voted him Miss Congeniality, and he was crowned in the season finale.<ref name=futoncritic1>{{cite news|title=Logo's ''RuPaul's Drag Race'' Season Four Reunion Wins the Crown as Highest-Rated Episode This Season |url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2012/05/02/logos-rupauls-drag-race-season-four-reunion-wins-the-crown-as-highest-rated-episode-this-season-199304/20120502logo01/|accessdate=December 11, 2014|publisher=The Futon Critic|date=May 2, 2012}}</ref>\n\nAfter coming into the public eye, Wilcots was ordained as a [[Minister (Christianity)|minister]]. The first wedding that he performed was for his friend Daniel in upstate New York in 2013. Royale is a supporter of marriage equality, though he believes that it should not be called \"gay marriage\", stating, \"It's a man and a man, and a woman and a woman getting married, and I think it is special and unique. So why not identify and celebrate it as something special and unique, and not lump it in with the same thing that has been going on for years?\"<ref name=dragofficial1>{{cite news|title=Exclusive Interview: Latrice Royale Talks 'Marriage' and Performing Her First Wedding|url=http://www.dragofficial.com/archives/exclusive-interview-latrice-royale-talks-marriage-and-performing-his-first-wedding|accessdate=December 12, 2014|publisher=Drag Official|date=July 10, 2013}}</ref><ref name=Robinson1>{{cite news|last1=Robinson|first1=Nicholas|title=Celebrity drag queen Latrice Royale gets ordained, marries gay couple|url=http://rollingout.com/culture/celebrity-drag-queen-latrice-royale-gets-ordained-marries-gay-couple/#_|accessdate=December 12, 2014|publisher=Rolling Out|date=July 12, 2013}}</ref>\n\n===''RuPaul's Drag Race'' season 4===\nLatrice Royale competed as a \"[[Plus-size model|plus-size]]\" [[Drag queen|queen]].<ref name=Hines1>{{cite news|last1=Hines|first1=Emily Bartlett|title=In anticipation of her New Year's Eve gig at Play, Latrice Royale talks girdles, gospel and goddesses|url=http://www.nashvillescene.com/nashville/in-anticipation-of-her-new-years-eve-gig-at-play-latrice-royale-talks-girdles-gospel-and-goddesses/Content?oid=3203635|accessdate=December 13, 2014|publisher=Nashville Scene Magazine|date=December 27, 2012}}</ref> He competed against twelve other queens, including [[Sharon Needles]], [[Phi Phi O'Hara]], [[Willam Belli]], and [[Cher]] impersonator [[Chad Michaels]].<ref name=JohnsonLisa>{{cite news|last1=Johnson|first1=Lisa|title=RuPaul\u2019s Drag Race Season Four Cast Revealed|url=http://www.bet.com/news/celebrities/2011/11/15/get-set-rupaul-s-drag-race-season-4-cast-revealed.html|accessdate=12 December 2014|publisher=BET|date=15 Nov 2011}}</ref>\n\nRoyale made it into the top four\u2014along with Needles, Michaels, and O'Hara\u2014and won two [[RuPaul's Drag Race#Format|challenges]] along the way, including when she acted in a mock sitcom in [[Queens Behind Bars]]. When Royale was cut from the competition, ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' called the elimination \"shocking\".<ref name=Stransky1>{{cite news|last1=Stransky|first1=Tanner|title='RuPaul's Drag Race' contestant Latrice Royale talks elimination, Sharon Needles, and what's next|url=http://popwatch.ew.com/2012/04/18/rupauls-drag-race-latrice-royale-eliminated/|accessdate= December 11, 2014|publisher=Entertainment Weekly|date=April 18, 2012}}</ref> When he was eliminated, Royale said to show host [[RuPaul]], \"You have changed my life forever. You have changed the world of drag forever. I love you and respect you so much, and thank you for seeing something special in me. Thank you.\" Guest judges in attendance were [[Wynonna Judd]] and [[Rose McGowan]]; Royale's words brought tears to McGowan's eyes.<ref name=rosemcgowan1>{{cite news|title='RuPaul's Drag Race': Rose McGowan And Wynonna Judd Sit In On An Emotional Goodbye (VIDEO)|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/04/10/rupauls-drag-race-rose-mcgowan-wynonna-judd-video_n_1414120.html|accessdate= December 11, 2014|publisher=Huffington Post|date= December 10, 2014}}</ref><ref name=Stransky2>{{cite news |last1=Stransky |first1=Tanner |title=''RuPaul's Drag Race'' shocker! A beloved queen is eliminated... |url=http://popwatch.ew.com/2012/04/09/rupauls-drag-race-season-4-episode-11/|accessdate=December 11, 2014 |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |date= April 9, 2012}}</ref>\n\nSharon Needles won the crown for season 4. In the season finale, it was announced that Royale would appear on ''RuPaul's Drag U'', which aired later that year.<ref name=\"du\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.newnownext.com/rupaul-drag-u-latrice-royale-beauty-tips/06/2012/|title='RuPaul's Drag U': Latrice Royale Beauty Tips|publisher=Logo|access-date=2018-10-07}}</ref>\n\n===''RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars'' season 1===\n[[File:Latrice Royale.jpg|thumb|right|Royale performing in June 2013]]\nAfter ''RuPaul's Drag Race'', Royale went on tour across the United States, performing at a number of different venues. When he had the opportunity to appear on ''RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars'', Royale had to cancel tour dates to appear in the show.<ref name=Hines1 />\n\nFor ''All Stars'', Royale competed against Chad Michaels, [[Raven (drag queen)|Raven]], [[Jujubee (drag queen)|Jujubee]], Shannel, [[Alexis Mateo]], [[Yara Sofia]], [[Manila Luzon]], [[Nina Flowers]], [[Tammie Brown]], [[Pandora Boxx]], and [[Mimi Imfurst]].<ref name=Armbrister1>{{cite news|last1=Armbrister|first1=Dey|title=\u2018RuPaul\u2019s All Stars Drag Race\u2019: Meet the Queens|url=http://www.newnownext.com/rupauls-all-stars-drag-race-meet-the-queens/08/2012/|accessdate=December 10, 2014|publisher=New Now Next|date= August 6, 2012}}</ref> For the competition, the queens were paired together, which was a departure from the rest of the RuPaul competitions where everyone competed alone. Royale and Luzon both chose to be together, and as a team they won the first challenge of the season.\n\nOn the third episode of the season, after not performing well with the street-punking challenge, Luzon and Jujubee faced off in the lip syncing challenge to represent each of their teams. Jujubee was paired with Raven. In the end, Royale and Luzon were sent home.<ref name=Garvey1>{{cite news|last1=Garvey|first1=Georgia|title=RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars: Streetwalkers|url=http://articles.redeyechicago.com/2012-11-06/entertainment/34954350_1_chad-michaels-homeless-man-latrice-royale|accessdate= December 12, 2014|publisher=Red Eye Chicago|date= November 2012}}</ref> About the two leaving, RuPaul told them, \"Manila and Latrice, my brainy and courageous queens. I think I\u2019m going to miss you the most. Now, sashay away.\"<ref name=Stransky3>{{cite news|last1=Stransky|first1=Tanner|title='RuPaul's Drag Race: All Stars' episode 3: Did [spoiler] really deserve to go home?|url=http://popwatch.ew.com/2012/11/05/rupauls-all-stars-drag-race-episode-3/|accessdate= December 12, 2014|work=Entertainment Weekly|date= November 5, 2012}}</ref>\n\n===''RuPaul's Drag U''===\nIn 2012, Royale joined the cast of ''RuPaul's Drag U'' for its [[RuPaul's Drag U#Season 3|third]] and final season. Other \"professors\" included:  JuJubee, Manila Luzon, Raja, Raven, Shannel, Alexis Mateo, [[Mariah (drag queen)|Mariah]], Chad Michaels, Willam, [[Morgan McMichaels]], Pandora Boxx, [[Delta Work]] and Sharon Needles.<ref name=Robertson1>{{cite news|last1=Robertson|first1=Lindsay|title=And The \u2018RuPaul\u2019s Drag U\u2019 Season 3 Professors Are\u2026|url=http://www.newnownext.com/and-the-rupauls-drag-u-season-3-professors-are/05/2012/|accessdate=December 12, 2014|publisher=LOGO TV|date=14 May 2012}}</ref>\n\n===Other performances===\nIn January 2014, Royale released his debut single \"[[Weight (song)|Weight]]\", which was endorsed by [[Logo TV]].<ref name=averyweight>{{cite news|last1=Avery|first1=Dan|title=Latrice Royale Releases New Chunky-Yet-Funky Single, \"Weight\": LISTEN|url=http://www.newnownext.com/latrice-royale-releases-new-chunky-yet-funky-single-weight-listen/01/2014/|accessdate=December 12, 2014|publisher=New Now Next|date= January 15, 2014}}</ref> A remix EP was released in March that year.<ref>{{Citation|title=Weight Remixes by Latrice Royale on iTunes|date=2014-03-20|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/weight-remixes/843303348|language=en-US|access-date=2018-11-10}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2014, Royale introduced and then performed with [[Jennifer Hudson]] at the [[CBS]] [[Fashion Rocks]] charity fundraiser event. Hudson stated that working with Royale \"Gave me life.\"<ref name=newnownext1>{{cite news|last1=Avery|first1=Dan|title=Jennifer Hudson: Performing With Latrice Royale \"Gave Me Life\"|url=http://www.newnownext.com/jennifer-hudson/09/2014/|accessdate= December 10, 2014|publisher=New Now Next|date= September 25, 2014}}</ref><ref name=Avery2>{{cite news|last1=Avery|first1=Dan|title=Latrice Royale Tears Up CBS\u2019 Fashion Rocks With Jennifer Hudson|url=http://www.newnownext.com/latrice-royale-tears-up-cbs-fashion-rocks-with-jennifer-hudson/09/2014/|accessdate=December 10, 2014|publisher=Logo|date=September 11, 2014}}</ref>\n\nRoyale works at the Palace Bar in [[South Beach]], Florida. Of working there, Royale stated, \"I love this place NOT because I work there, but because it is the Ultimate Experience.. It\u2019s outside right on the Beach. Beautiful People, Great Food/Drinks and the Drag Shows are amazing!\"<ref name=keyesjeff>{{cite news|last1=Keyes|first1=Jeffrey James|title=A Drag Race Christmas: Latrice Royale|url=http://www.queerty.com/latriceroyale-20111219|accessdate=December 13, 2014|publisher=Queerty}}</ref><ref name=palacepeople1>{{cite news|title=Latrice Royale|url=http://palacesouthbeach.com/artists/latrice-royal-2/|accessdate= December 13, 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Royale appeared alongside [[Peaches Christ]] and ''RuPaul's Drag Race'' alum [[Willam]] in ''Mister Act,'' an off-Broadway gender-flipped parody of the film [[Sister Act]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/fort-lauderdale/article/BWW-Reviews-MISTER-ACT-A-Hilarious-Spoof-Done-Right-20180207|title=BWW Reviews: MISTER ACT A Hilarious Spoof Done Right|last=Durham|first=Trevor|work=BroadwayWorld.com|access-date=2018-10-07|language=en}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2016, Royale released her EP, ''Here's to Life: Latrice Royale Live in the Studio'', produced by [[Roman Molino Dunn|Electropoint]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Dalton|first1=Paisley|title=Latrice Royale Gets Jazzy With It on Debut Album \"Here\u2019s To Life\"|url=http://worldofwonder.net/latrice-royale-gets-jazzy-with-it-on-debut-album-heres-to-life/|publisher=World of Wonder|accessdate=February 8, 2017}}</ref> In 2018 and 2019, Royale took ''Here's to Life'' on tour and performed her [[Shirley Horn|Shirley Horne]]-inspired act in cities across Canada and the United States.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailyxtra.com/the-gospel-of-truth-according-to-latrice-royale-159112|title=The gospel of truth according to Latrice Royale|date=2019-07-05|website=Xtra|access-date=2020-02-07}}</ref> \n\nShe competed in the Drag Race television special ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race Holi-slay Spectacular]]''.<ref name=holislay>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/pride/8482663/rupauls-drag-race-holiday-spectacular-trixie-shangela|title=Kim Chi, Shangela, Trixie Mattel & More to Compete in 'RuPaul's Drag Race Holi-Slay Spectacular'|work=Billboard|access-date=2018-11-02}}</ref>\n\n===''RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars'' season 4===\n\nIn November 2018, Royale was announced as a cast member for  ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars (season 4)|All Stars 4]]'', joining fellow ''All Stars'' season 1 cast member [[Manila Luzon]] for his second ''All Stars'' competition; the pair are the first ''Drag Race'' alumni to compete on two ''All Stars'' seasons. They are also the second and third contestants to compete on three separate seasons of the show (excluding specials) following [[Shangela Laquifa Wadley]]. Royale was originally eliminated fourth, sent home by [[Monique Heart]], but was brought back into the competition during the LalapaRuza episode.<ref name=\"Blanton\">{{cite news |last1=Blanton |first1=Kayla |title=Latrice Royale's Return On 'All Stars' 4 Could've Been Ru's Plan All Along |url=https://www.bustle.com/p/latrice-royales-return-on-all-stars-4-couldve-been-rus-plan-all-along-15837151 |accessdate=19 January 2019 |publisher=Bustle |date=18 January 2019}}</ref> After her elimination she won episode seven and eliminated [[Valentina (drag queen)|Valentina]] from the competition. She was eliminated for good in episode nine by [[Trinity Taylor|Trinity The Tuck]], placing fifth.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tvline.com/2019/02/08/rupauls-drag-race-recap-latrice-royale-eliminated-all-stars-4-episode-9/|title=RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars Recap: Was the Right Queen Carried Away?|last=Swift|first=Andy|last2=Swift|first2=Andy|date=2019-02-09|website=TVLine|language=en|access-date=2019-02-09}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nWilcots proposed to Christopher Hamblin in June 2016.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.newnownext.com/latrice-royale-proposes-to-boyfriend/06/2016/|title=Latrice Royale Proposes To Boyfriend On Stage In Seattle|work=LOGO News|access-date=2018-10-07}}</ref> The couple were married in Atlanta, Georgia on September 29, 2018 (with Wilcots out of drag). Attendees included ''Drag Race'' alumni and other drag performers.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Vu |first1=Lily |title=Drag Star Latrice Royale Got Hitched This Weekend! |url=https://www.dragstarusa.com/latrice-royale-wedding/ |website=DragStarUSA.com |accessdate=October 18, 2018 |date= October 3, 2018}}</ref> After the [[2018 United States elections]], Wilcots gained his right to vote again.<ref name=\"votingrights\">{{cite news |last1=Dawson |first1=Lamar |title=Latrice Royale Reflects On Restoration of Voting Rights |url=http://www.newnownext.com/latrice-royale-reflects-on-restoration-of-voting-rights/11/2018/ |accessdate=19 January 2019 |publisher=NewNowNext |date=9 November 2018}}</ref>\n\nWilcots is a Christian.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B_mu0w0HAJ4</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n\n=== EPs ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\"| Details\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''The Chop Remixes''\n|\n*Released: December 26, 2012\n*Label: N/A\n*Formats: Digital download\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Weight Remixes''\n|\n*Released: March 20, 2014\n*Label: LOMLPLEX\n*Formats: Digital download\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Here's to Life: Latrice Royale Live in the Studio''\n|\n*Released: March 10, 2016\n*Label: LRI Talent & Management\n*Formats: Digital download\n|}\n\n=== Singles ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"