{"title_page": "Bucelas", "text_new": "{{Infobox Portuguese subdivision \n|type = parish \n|official_name      = Bucelas\n|image_skyline      = \n|image_caption      = \n|image_flag         =\n|image_shield       = \n|image_location     = \n|region             = [[Lisboa Region|Lisbon]]\n|metro              = [[Lisbon metropolitan area|Lisbon]]\n|district           = [[Lisbon District|Lisbon]]\n|municipality       = [[Loures]]\n|coordinates        = {{coord|38.901|-9.119|type:adm1st_region:PT_dim:50000|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation          = \n|area_total         = 33.97\n|population_as_of   = 2011\n|population_total   = 4663\n|patron             = \n|area_code          = \n|postal_code        = \n|website            = \n}}\n'''Bucelas''' is a [[Freguesia (Portugal)|civil parish]] in the municipality of [[Loures]], Portugal.<ref>{{cite web|title=Law nr. 11-A/2013, page 552 62|url=http://dre.pt/pdf1sdip/2013/01/01901/0000200147.pdf |accessdate=24 July 2014|author=Di\u00e1rio da Rep\u00fablica|language=Portuguese|author-link=Di\u00e1rio da Rep\u00fablica }}</ref> The population in 2011 was 4,663,<ref name=ine>[http://www.ine.pt/ngt_server/attachfileu.jsp?look_parentBoui=165404348&att_display=n&att_download=y Instituto Nacional de Estat\u00edstica (INE)], Census 2011 results according to the 2013 administrative division of Portugal</ref> in an area of 33.97&nbsp;km\u00b2 (13.12&nbsp;sq mi).<ref name=dgt>{{Cite web |url=http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ |title=\u00c1reas das freguesias, concelhos, distritos e pa\u00eds |access-date=2018-11-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181105172426/http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ |archive-date=2018-11-05 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nThe town is known for its [[Bucelas DOC]] wine. A museum in the centre of the town [https://www.cm-loures.pt/AreaConteudo.aspx?DisplayId=894] gives a good description of the history of the industry and also exhibits some of the equipment used. The museum also has a section devoted to the [[Lines of Torres Vedras]], which were defensive lines built by Anglo-Portuguese forces in 1809-10 to protect [[Lisbon]] from invading French troops during the [[Peninsular War]]. Some of the forts close to Bucelas, such as the [[Fort of Arpim]], the [[Fort of Ribas]] and the [[Forts of Ajuda|Fort of Ajuda Grande]], have been restored.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Parishes of Loures Municipality}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Parishes of Loures]]\n\n\n{{Lisbon-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Portuguese subdivision \n|type = parish \n|official_name      = Bucelas\n|image_skyline      = \n|image_caption      = \n|image_flag         =\n|image_shield       = \n|image_location     = \n|region             = [[Lisboa Region|Lisbon]]\n|metro              = [[Lisbon metropolitan area|Lisbon]]\n|district           = [[Lisbon District|Lisbon]]\n|municipality       = [[Loures]]\n|coordinates        = {{coord|38.901|-9.119|type:adm1st_region:PT_dim:50000|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation          = \n|area_total         = 33.97\n|population_as_of   = 2011\n|population_total   = 4663\n|patron             = \n|area_code          = \n|postal_code        = \n|website            = \n}}\n'''Bucelas''' is a [[Freguesia (Portugal)|civil parish]] in the municipality of [[Loures]], Portugal.<ref>{{cite web|title=Law nr. 11-A/2013, page 552 62|url=http://dre.pt/pdf1sdip/2013/01/01901/0000200147.pdf |accessdate=24 July 2014|author=Di\u00e1rio da Rep\u00fablica|language=Portuguese|author-link=Di\u00e1rio da Rep\u00fablica }}</ref> The population in 2011 was 4,663,<ref name=ine>[http://www.ine.pt/ngt_server/attachfileu.jsp?look_parentBoui=165404348&att_display=n&att_download=y Instituto Nacional de Estat\u00edstica (INE)], Census 2011 results according to the 2013 administrative division of Portugal</ref> in an area of 33.97&nbsp;km\u00b2 (13.12&nbsp;sq mi).<ref name=dgt>{{Cite web |url=http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ |title=\u00c1reas das freguesias, concelhos, distritos e pa\u00eds |access-date=2018-11-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181105172426/http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ |archive-date=2018-11-05 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nThe town is known for its [[Bucelas DOC]] wine. A museum in the centre of the town [https://www.cm-loures.pt/AreaConteudo.aspx?DisplayId=894] gives a good description of the history of the industry and also exhibits some of the equipment used. The museum also has a section devoted to the [[Lines of Torres Vedras]], which were defensive lines built by Anglo-Portuguese forces in 1809-10 to protect [[Lisbon]] from invading French troops during the [[Peninsular War]]. Some of the forts close to Bucelas, such as the [[Fort of Arpim]], the [[Fort of Ribas]] and the [[Forts of Ajuda|Fort of Ajuda Grande]], have been restored.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Parishes of Loures Municipality}}\n\n[[Category:Parishes of Loures]]\n\n\n{{Lisbon-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bucelas"}
{"title_page": "Buarcos", "text_new": "{{Infobox Portuguese subdivision \n|type = parish\n|official_name      = Buarcos\n|image_skyline      = \n|image_caption      = \n|image_flag         =\n|image_shield       = \n|image_location     = \n|region             = [[Centro Region, Portugal|Centro]]\n|CIM                = [[Regi\u00e3o de Coimbra]]\n|district           = [[Coimbra District|Coimbra]]\n|municipality       = [[Figueira da Foz]]\n|coordinates        = {{coord|40.166|-8.877|type:adm1st_region:PT_dim:50000|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation          = \n|area_total         = 15.53\n|population_as_of   = 2011\n|population_total   = 18454\n|patron             = \n|area_code          = \n|postal_code        = \n|website            = \n}}\n'''Buarcos''' is a ''[[freguesia]]'' (civil parish) in [[Figueira da Foz Municipality]], Portugal. The population in 2011 was 18,454,<ref name=ine>[http://www.ine.pt/ngt_server/attachfileu.jsp?look_parentBoui=165404348&att_display=n&att_download=y Instituto Nacional de Estat\u00edstica (INE)], Census 2011 results according to the 2013 administrative division of Portugal</ref> in an area of 15.53&nbsp;km\u00b2.<ref name=dgt>{{Cite web |url=http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ |title=\u00c1reas das freguesias, concelhos, distritos e pa\u00eds |access-date=2018-11-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181105172426/http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ |archive-date=2018-11-05 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nDuring the 1600s, the people of Buarcos were harassed by pirates and built the long fortification that stands to this day. It is a traditional fishing town that has grown also as a noted beach resort, likely the most beautiful of Portugal, due to its wonderful landscape namely the beach which is protected by the Boa Viagem small mountain range (''Serra da Boa Viagem''). Many of its inhabitants still work in the fishing industry but tourism is also an important activity. It has many hotels, seafood restaurants and bars with view over the bay and the extensive beach. Buarcos is now considered one of the best tourism destinations within Europe.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Parishes of Figueira da Foz]]\n[[Category:Seaside resorts in Portugal]]\n\n\n{{Coimbra-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Portuguese subdivision \n|type = parish\n|official_name      = Buarcos\n|image_skyline      = \n|image_caption      = \n|image_flag         =\n|image_shield       = \n|image_location     = \n|region             = [[Centro Region, Portugal|Centro]]\n|CIM                = [[Regi\u00e3o de Coimbra]]\n|district           = [[Coimbra District|Coimbra]]\n|municipality       = [[Figueira da Foz]]\n|coordinates        = {{coord|40.166|-8.877|type:adm1st_region:PT_dim:50000|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation          = \n|area_total         = 15.53\n|population_as_of   = 2011\n|population_total   = 18454\n|patron             = \n|area_code          = \n|postal_code        = \n|website            = \n}}\n'''Buarcos''' is a ''[[freguesia]]'' (civil parish) in [[Figueira da Foz Municipality]], Portugal. The population in 2011 was 18,454,<ref name=ine>[http://www.ine.pt/ngt_server/attachfileu.jsp?look_parentBoui=165404348&att_display=n&att_download=y Instituto Nacional de Estat\u00edstica (INE)], Census 2011 results according to the 2013 administrative division of Portugal</ref> in an area of 15.53&nbsp;km\u00b2.<ref name=dgt>{{Cite web |url=http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ |title=\u00c1reas das freguesias, concelhos, distritos e pa\u00eds |access-date=2018-11-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181105172426/http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ |archive-date=2018-11-05 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nDuring the 1600s, the people of Buarcos were harassed by pirates and built the long fortification that stands to this day. It is a traditional fishing town that has grown also as a noted beach resort, likely the most beautiful of Portugal, due to its wonderful landscape namely the beach which is protected by the Boa Viagem small mountain range (''Serra da Boa Viagem''). Many of its inhabitants still work in the fishing industry but tourism is also an important activity. It has many hotels, seafood restaurants and bars with view over the bay and the extensive beach. Buarcos is now considered one of the best tourism destinations within Europe.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Parishes of Figueira da Foz]]\n[[Category:Seaside resorts in Portugal]]\n\n\n{{Coimbra-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Buarcos"}
{"title_page": "Brito (Guimar\u00e3es)", "text_new": "{{Infobox Portuguese subdivision \n|type = parish \n|official_name      = Brito\n|image_flag = Pt-gmrbt1.PNG\n|image_shield = GMR-brito.PNG\n|image_skyline      = \n|image_caption      = \n|image_location     = GMR-brito_mapa.PNG\n|region             = [[Norte Region, Portugal|Norte]]\n|CIM                = [[Ave (intermunicipal community)|Ave]]\n|district           = [[Braga District|Braga]]\n|municipality       = [[Guimar\u00e3es]]\n|coordinates        = {{coord|41.453|-8.366|type:adm1st_region:PT_dim:50000|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation          =\n|area_total         = 5.90\n|population_as_of   = 2011\n|population_total   = 4939\n|patron             =\n|area_code          = \n|postal_code        = \n|website            = [http://freg-brito.com Junta de freguesia de Brito]\n}}\n'''Brito''' is a [[Freguesia (Portugal)|civil parish]] in the municipality of [[Guimar\u00e3es Municipality|Guimar\u00e3es]] in the [[Braga District]] of [[Portugal]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Law nr. 11-A/2013, pages 552 57-58|url=http://dre.pt/pdf1sdip/2013/01/01901/0000200147.pdf |accessdate=5 August 2014|author=''[[Di\u00e1rio da Rep\u00fablica]]''|language=Portuguese|format=pdf}}</ref> The population in 2011 was 4,939,<ref name=ine>[http://www.ine.pt/xportal/xmain?xlang=en&xpid=INE&xpgid=ine_indicadores&indOcorrCod=0005889&contexto=pi&selTab=tab0 Instituto Nacional de Estat\u00edstica]</ref> in an area of 5.90&nbsp;km\u00b2.<ref name=dgt>{{Cite web |url=http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ |title=\u00c1reas das freguesias, concelhos, distritos e pa\u00eds |access-date=2018-11-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181105172426/http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ |archive-date=2018-11-05 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Brito (Guimaraes)}}\n[[Category:Parishes of Guimar\u00e3es]]\n\n\n{{Braga-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Portuguese subdivision \n|type = parish \n|official_name      = Brito\n|image_flag = Pt-gmrbt1.PNG\n|image_shield = GMR-brito.PNG\n|image_skyline      = \n|image_caption      = \n|image_location     = GMR-brito_mapa.PNG\n|region             = [[Norte Region, Portugal|Norte]]\n|CIM                = [[Ave (intermunicipal community)|Ave]]\n|district           = [[Braga District|Braga]]\n|municipality       = [[Guimar\u00e3es]]\n|coordinates        = {{coord|41.453|-8.366|type:adm1st_region:PT_dim:50000|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation          =\n|area_total         = 5.90\n|population_as_of   = 2011\n|population_total   = 4939\n|patron             =\n|area_code          = \n|postal_code        = \n|website            = [http://freg-brito.com Junta de freguesia de Brito]\n}}\n'''Brito''' is a [[Freguesia (Portugal)|civil parish]] in the municipality of [[Guimar\u00e3es Municipality|Guimar\u00e3es]] in the [[Braga District]] of [[Portugal]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Law nr. 11-A/2013, pages 552 57-58|url=http://dre.pt/pdf1sdip/2013/01/01901/0000200147.pdf |accessdate=5 August 2014|author=''[[Di\u00e1rio da Rep\u00fablica]]''|language=Portuguese|format=pdf}}</ref> The population in 2011 was 4,939,<ref name=ine>[http://www.ine.pt/xportal/xmain?xlang=en&xpid=INE&xpgid=ine_indicadores&indOcorrCod=0005889&contexto=pi&selTab=tab0 Instituto Nacional de Estat\u00edstica]</ref> in an area of 5.90&nbsp;km\u00b2.<ref name=dgt>{{Cite web |url=http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ |title=\u00c1reas das freguesias, concelhos, distritos e pa\u00eds |access-da